[00:01] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'A new model, “Microsoft Lens,” has been&nbsp; released, and the model is great for&nbsp;&nbsp; systems with smaller graphics memory. The images were trained with decent&nbsp;&nbsp; captions generated by GPT, so this model&nbsp; should understand the prompt better.&nbsp; These are the sample images, and the images this&nbsp; model generates are not restricted to 1024 pixels.'

[00:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The model is available on Hugging Face, and these&nbsp; are the original links to the model weights.&nbsp; Below is the directory to place&nbsp; these models, given for Comfy UI.&nbsp;'

[00:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'These are the three files required&nbsp; to generate text-to-image.&nbsp; Inside the diffusion model folder,&nbsp; there are two types of models.&nbsp;'

[00:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'The first is the base model, which&nbsp; requires 50 steps to generate a&nbsp;&nbsp; final image with a CFG value of 5. And the second is the turbo model,&nbsp;&nbsp; which should give us an image with&nbsp; in 8 steps with a CFG value of 1.0'

[00:56] [scene:talk]
