[07:17] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'where I was using a LoRa, which&nbsp; made the final result better.&nbsp; I have updated the same workflow by adding&nbsp; a similar image-to-image workflow where the&nbsp;&nbsp; image from HiDream will be processed&nbsp; again using a Z-image turbo model.'

[07:30] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'Now I can use the image editing capabilities of&nbsp; HiDream and can also get a detailed image from it.&nbsp; The denoising value is at 35 percent;&nbsp; increasing this will allow the model&nbsp;&nbsp;'

[07:42] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'to make more changes in the subject.&nbsp; So, make sure to keep this below 40.&nbsp; This image got overcooked&nbsp; due to the number of steps.'

[07:54] [scene:talk]
VISUAL:
AUDIO: 'I am using the HiDream Dev model,&nbsp; which is a distilled model. 30&nbsp;&nbsp; steps are enough for the final image. Keep it above 30 when using the base model.&nbsp; Also, make sure to look at the CFG, which&nbsp; should be at 1 when using the distilled model.&nbsp;'

[08:10] [scene:talk]
